1
00:00:30,760 --> 00:00:31,600
Lak.

2
00:00:39,480 --> 00:00:41,120
<i>Please don't do this, Sin.</i>

3
00:00:43,880 --> 00:00:44,800
Lak?

4
00:00:52,040 --> 00:00:52,960
Lak?

5
00:01:01,760 --> 00:01:03,880
Sin, what are you trying to do?

6
00:01:09,360 --> 00:01:11,720
Lak, I…

7
00:01:12,920 --> 00:01:17,320
The Sin I know
would never do something like this.

8
00:01:20,600 --> 00:01:21,520
But…

9
00:01:22,880 --> 00:01:24,240
I have to take back everything…

10
00:01:25,520 --> 00:01:27,480
everything that belongs to our family.

11
00:01:29,160 --> 00:01:31,720
By assaulting someone
who can't fight back?

12
00:01:35,560 --> 00:01:37,040
Sin,

13
00:01:37,640 --> 00:01:39,720
harassing others

14
00:01:39,800 --> 00:01:41,720
isn't hard,

15
00:01:41,800 --> 00:01:45,280
especially when it's someone defenseless.

16
00:01:45,360 --> 00:01:48,320
Lak, I have to do this.

17
00:01:49,640 --> 00:01:52,360
You're doing it just because

18
00:01:52,440 --> 00:01:55,720
she's not your family, not your mother,

19
00:01:56,360 --> 00:02:00,080
not your sister, is that it?

20
00:02:01,080 --> 00:02:02,960
If someone did this to me,

21
00:02:04,120 --> 00:02:06,120
how would you feel?

22
00:02:07,200 --> 00:02:10,639
Lak, but they destroyed our family.

23
00:02:10,720 --> 00:02:13,480
I have to destroy her dignity.

24
00:02:28,760 --> 00:02:30,280
What you're doing,

25
00:02:31,160 --> 00:02:33,840
are you destroying someone else's dignity,

26
00:02:34,640 --> 00:02:36,920
or your own?

27
00:02:41,400 --> 00:02:42,800
Lak, I…

28
00:02:45,240 --> 00:02:46,480
I…

29
00:02:48,040 --> 00:02:51,000
If you're still the same Sin

30
00:02:51,080 --> 00:02:52,360
that I respect,

31
00:02:55,920 --> 00:02:57,880
I'll always stand by your side.

32
00:03:03,200 --> 00:03:04,320
Lak.

33
00:05:52,120 --> 00:05:53,240
Sin.

34
00:05:54,440 --> 00:05:55,640
Aunt Nong.

35
00:05:55,720 --> 00:05:59,800
<i>Sin, why didn't you pick up my calls</i>
<i>last night? I called you so many times.</i>

36
00:06:00,480 --> 00:06:03,520
What's wrong? Why are you crying?

37
00:06:03,600 --> 00:06:05,520
Who did this to you?

38
00:06:05,600 --> 00:06:09,120
Aunt Nong, I saw Lak.

39
00:06:09,200 --> 00:06:10,160
<i>Lak…</i>

40
00:06:11,640 --> 00:06:14,200
Lak came to see me.

41
00:06:14,280 --> 00:06:16,840
<i>Lak has been dead for a long time, Sin.</i>

42
00:06:18,240 --> 00:06:21,360
Sin, come home, okay?

43
00:06:21,440 --> 00:06:23,840
We'll talk at home. It's alright.

44
00:06:24,440 --> 00:06:25,720
Aunt Nong, I…

45
00:06:26,600 --> 00:06:29,640
I failed.

46
00:06:29,720 --> 00:06:31,640
<i>What did you fail at?</i>

47
00:06:33,640 --> 00:06:36,080
I couldn't do what I planned.

48
00:06:37,760 --> 00:06:40,880
It's okay. I told you,

49
00:06:40,960 --> 00:06:43,600
I'll take care of everything for you.

50
00:06:43,680 --> 00:06:45,680
<i>Don't be afraid.</i>

51
00:06:45,760 --> 00:06:48,040
Aunt Nong, please help me.

52
00:06:48,640 --> 00:06:51,440
Everything that should belong to you

53
00:06:52,480 --> 00:06:54,240
has to be yours.

54
00:06:59,920 --> 00:07:01,960
Yes, Aunt Nong.

55
00:07:20,760 --> 00:07:22,760
Transfer the money,
and I'll tell you where she is.

56
00:07:22,840 --> 00:07:23,920
Fine.

57
00:07:27,400 --> 00:07:29,240
Aren't we going to follow Mr. Warat?

58
00:07:29,320 --> 00:07:30,760
And Kluay…

59
00:07:31,760 --> 00:07:35,760
Som, we have to trust Mr. Warat.
We have to believe in him.

60
00:07:37,240 --> 00:07:40,280
Because there's something
we need to finish first.

61
00:07:47,440 --> 00:07:51,080
Hello, Attorney.
This is Arnon, Mr. Warat's assistant.

62
00:07:51,160 --> 00:07:53,280
Mr. Warat wants to
transfer all his shares.

63
00:07:54,840 --> 00:07:56,880
Mrs. Wanee has approved it.

64
00:07:58,840 --> 00:08:00,360
Mr. Warat

65
00:08:00,440 --> 00:08:05,240
wants to transfer everything
to the rightful heir of the Vanich family.

66
00:08:05,320 --> 00:08:09,400
Please prepare the documents.

67
00:08:09,480 --> 00:08:12,680
I'll come review them myself
at Vanich house

68
00:08:12,760 --> 00:08:14,800
before Mr. Warat signs.

69
00:08:23,920 --> 00:08:25,080
Mr. Rut,

70
00:08:26,040 --> 00:08:27,920
I'm on my way to pick you up.

71
00:08:28,000 --> 00:08:29,680
<i>What time will you be here?</i>

72
00:08:29,760 --> 00:08:32,039
In about an hour.

73
00:08:32,120 --> 00:08:35,240
Please ask the nurse to prepare the bill.

74
00:08:35,320 --> 00:08:37,000
Where's Sin?

75
00:08:37,080 --> 00:08:39,640
He has something to take care of.

76
00:08:39,720 --> 00:08:43,799
Something to take care of?
And you're coming alone by taxi?

77
00:08:45,280 --> 00:08:46,120
Yes.

78
00:08:46,200 --> 00:08:49,440
<i>What could be so important?</i>

79
00:08:52,280 --> 00:08:56,560
He's handling Mr. Warat's matter for you.

80
00:08:57,560 --> 00:08:58,640
<i>Alright.</i>

81
00:08:59,720 --> 00:09:02,240
I'll be there soon.

82
00:09:09,440 --> 00:09:12,680
BUNYAVEJ HOSPITAL

83
00:09:15,840 --> 00:09:19,400
What's Sin doing so early?

84
00:09:19,480 --> 00:09:21,120
He's taking care of something for you.

85
00:09:21,200 --> 00:09:22,920
I'm going to be rich soon.

86
00:09:24,080 --> 00:09:26,120
Warat has received the shares.

87
00:09:26,200 --> 00:09:29,840
And he already knows I'm his real father.

88
00:09:34,040 --> 00:09:35,240
Maybe

89
00:09:36,200 --> 00:09:39,720
being here alone

90
00:09:39,800 --> 00:09:42,480
made me think about many things.

91
00:09:43,440 --> 00:09:44,680
Like what?

92
00:09:45,320 --> 00:09:46,680
All this time,

93
00:09:47,480 --> 00:09:49,680
I may have been too harsh on Sin.

94
00:09:51,320 --> 00:09:52,520
Believe it or not,

95
00:09:53,520 --> 00:09:54,960
he's been taking care of me.

96
00:09:55,680 --> 00:09:58,480
He brought me to the hospital
when you weren't around.

97
00:10:00,760 --> 00:10:02,000
- That's good.
- Mm.

98
00:10:06,240 --> 00:10:07,840
Maybe

99
00:10:07,920 --> 00:10:10,760
I should do

100
00:10:10,840 --> 00:10:13,120
more good things for him.

101
00:10:15,480 --> 00:10:16,880
Don't worry.

102
00:10:17,800 --> 00:10:20,800
You'll get the chance to do that soon.

103
00:10:21,960 --> 00:10:23,240
I believe so.

104
00:10:39,880 --> 00:10:40,800
Oh.

105
00:10:40,880 --> 00:10:42,760
- You're up early.
- Yes.

106
00:10:42,840 --> 00:10:45,960
Please have a seat for a moment.
Mr. Arnon will be here shortly.

107
00:10:46,040 --> 00:10:47,560
Alright.

108
00:10:47,640 --> 00:10:48,880
- Be my guest.
- Alright.

109
00:10:52,960 --> 00:10:55,600
<i>I hear Mr. Warat</i>
<i>is transferring his shares to someone.</i>

110
00:11:13,080 --> 00:11:14,800
I'll ask you one last time.

111
00:11:15,840 --> 00:11:17,760
I'm going to ask you one last time.

112
00:11:18,880 --> 00:11:20,400
Did you cause Lak's death?

113
00:11:22,680 --> 00:11:24,520
Do you know

114
00:11:25,520 --> 00:11:28,120
what Lak said

115
00:11:30,720 --> 00:11:32,640
before she died that morning?

116
00:11:45,840 --> 00:11:48,040
Lak, aren't you done yet?

117
00:11:48,840 --> 00:11:52,080
The professor said four o'clock sharp.

118
00:11:52,160 --> 00:11:54,160
If you go home,
he won't accept it anymore.

119
00:11:54,240 --> 00:11:56,400
- Really?
- Yeah.

120
00:11:56,480 --> 00:11:58,200
- Here, let me help you.
- Hey.

121
00:11:58,280 --> 00:12:00,120
No, it's okay. I want to finish it myself.

122
00:12:00,960 --> 00:12:02,000
Are you sure?

123
00:12:02,080 --> 00:12:04,360
- Mm.
- Fine.

124
00:12:04,960 --> 00:12:06,040
Fine.

125
00:12:07,720 --> 00:12:09,520
This one looks nice.

126
00:12:10,480 --> 00:12:11,480
Right?

127
00:12:12,400 --> 00:12:13,440
What's the concept?

128
00:12:14,480 --> 00:12:16,840
It's a house that…

129
00:12:18,040 --> 00:12:21,680
when I graduate and save enough money,

130
00:12:21,760 --> 00:12:23,480
I'm going to build this house for real.

131
00:12:24,920 --> 00:12:27,360
- It looks nice.
- Mm.

132
00:12:28,480 --> 00:12:29,560
This room…

133
00:12:31,280 --> 00:12:33,040
is for Sin.

134
00:12:33,120 --> 00:12:35,040
Sin lives there too?

135
00:12:35,120 --> 00:12:38,680
Of course. There's only us.

136
00:12:38,760 --> 00:12:40,440
We'll stay together forever.

137
00:12:40,520 --> 00:12:43,800
You really love him, don't you?
Do you ever fight?

138
00:12:44,400 --> 00:12:46,000
Sin and I

139
00:12:46,080 --> 00:12:49,320
have been through a lot together
to get here.

140
00:12:50,480 --> 00:12:52,120
From now on,

141
00:12:52,200 --> 00:12:54,280
I just want happiness.

142
00:12:58,560 --> 00:13:00,320
What should I do
about these signs you see?

143
00:13:02,720 --> 00:13:04,400
Maybe it's nothing.

144
00:13:04,480 --> 00:13:09,000
Maybe they're just warnings

145
00:13:09,080 --> 00:13:10,440
to live carefully.

146
00:13:14,160 --> 00:13:15,520
If something happens to me,

147
00:13:17,600 --> 00:13:19,360
please take care of him for me.

148
00:13:22,240 --> 00:13:25,840
Make sure he lives a happy life

149
00:13:25,920 --> 00:13:27,360
<i>for me.</i>

150
00:13:28,760 --> 00:13:29,760
Lak…

151
00:13:31,480 --> 00:13:32,800
Sin,

152
00:13:34,000 --> 00:13:36,600
whatever you're going to do,

153
00:13:37,880 --> 00:13:40,120
please think of Lak first.

154
00:13:49,440 --> 00:13:51,160
Kluay, are you in there?

155
00:13:51,880 --> 00:13:53,400
I'm here.

156
00:14:04,080 --> 00:14:07,320
Calm down. I'm the one who called you.

157
00:14:08,120 --> 00:14:09,280
Of course I'll open the door.

158
00:14:22,720 --> 00:14:23,960
The documents are incomplete.

159
00:14:24,040 --> 00:14:26,760
It was too sudden.
I couldn't prepare everything in time.

160
00:14:26,840 --> 00:14:28,880
I don't have complete information.

161
00:14:28,960 --> 00:14:29,880
What's missing?

162
00:14:29,960 --> 00:14:31,120
The transferee's name.

163
00:14:31,880 --> 00:14:33,720
Ms. Waree Vanich.

164
00:14:35,720 --> 00:14:37,560
Kluay, are you alright?

165
00:14:40,000 --> 00:14:43,200
Jirasin, stay away from Kluay.

166
00:14:43,960 --> 00:14:47,400
You want her that much?
She's useless to me now.

167
00:14:50,120 --> 00:14:51,040
Good.

168
00:14:52,400 --> 00:14:55,400
That way, you won't have to
mess with my woman again.

169
00:14:56,040 --> 00:14:57,240
I've already taken my revenge.

170
00:14:57,320 --> 00:14:58,520
Revenge?

171
00:14:59,320 --> 00:15:02,040
- What are you talking about?
- Your mom destroyed my family.

172
00:15:03,400 --> 00:15:06,280
Aunt Nong, Dad and Mom…

173
00:15:10,080 --> 00:15:11,640
They're in a good place now.

174
00:15:11,720 --> 00:15:14,720
What does that mean?

175
00:15:21,800 --> 00:15:23,480
Your mother told me

176
00:15:25,640 --> 00:15:28,440
to take good care of you.

177
00:15:29,360 --> 00:15:32,600
Then when will she come back?

178
00:15:42,600 --> 00:15:45,080
This never should have happened…

179
00:15:47,320 --> 00:15:50,320
None of this would've happened
if it weren't for that woman.

180
00:15:50,400 --> 00:15:51,960
For who?

181
00:15:52,040 --> 00:15:54,120
Praewilai.

182
00:15:54,200 --> 00:15:56,600
Since I was a child,
I've only ever heard two names,

183
00:15:56,680 --> 00:16:00,120
Praewilai, and you.
You're the reason my mother died!

184
00:16:00,200 --> 00:16:02,440
What you know, what you believe,

185
00:16:02,520 --> 00:16:04,120
it might not be true!

186
00:16:04,200 --> 00:16:06,400
It is true.
It's what I've believed all along.

187
00:16:06,480 --> 00:16:07,680
Okay.

188
00:16:08,800 --> 00:16:10,360
If that's what you think,

189
00:16:11,320 --> 00:16:13,720
I'm sorry. I'm sorry!

190
00:16:13,800 --> 00:16:15,720
You think saying sorry
will fix everything?

191
00:16:15,800 --> 00:16:17,400
Then what do you want me to do?

192
00:16:18,280 --> 00:16:19,760
You're stuck in the past,

193
00:16:20,800 --> 00:16:24,400
and you take it out on Kluay,
someone who knows nothing.

194
00:16:24,480 --> 00:16:25,560
Is that right?

195
00:16:27,520 --> 00:16:28,720
Let's go, Kluay.

196
00:16:31,840 --> 00:16:32,960
Then I guess I should apologize too.

197
00:16:35,880 --> 00:16:37,120
For the baby in Kluay's womb.

198
00:16:38,560 --> 00:16:40,000
What are you talking about, Sin?

199
00:16:40,520 --> 00:16:42,760
Kluay, don't you remember?

200
00:16:44,120 --> 00:16:45,520
We slept together last night.

201
00:16:46,200 --> 00:16:47,440
So what?

202
00:16:47,520 --> 00:16:50,880
If you want a woman with no dignity,

203
00:16:50,960 --> 00:16:53,000
someone worthless, then take her.

204
00:16:54,760 --> 00:16:56,600
I think you've got it all wrong.

205
00:16:56,680 --> 00:16:58,120
What did I get wrong?

206
00:16:58,200 --> 00:16:59,680
Listen carefully.

207
00:16:59,760 --> 00:17:03,280
I don't care whether
you actually slept with Kluay or not.

208
00:17:03,360 --> 00:17:07,000
Even if you did,
she didn't lose any dignity.

209
00:17:07,079 --> 00:17:09,040
The one who lost dignity is you.

210
00:17:09,560 --> 00:17:11,640
You lost your dignity as a man,

211
00:17:11,720 --> 00:17:14,440
using such dirty tactics on a woman.

212
00:17:16,720 --> 00:17:20,160
I'm serious, Sin.
What era do you think this is?

213
00:17:22,720 --> 00:17:25,680
Do you really think a woman's worth

214
00:17:26,960 --> 00:17:28,760
is just her virginity?

215
00:17:33,400 --> 00:17:34,800
Open your eyes.

216
00:17:36,760 --> 00:17:40,720
What you did is disgusting.

217
00:17:47,200 --> 00:17:48,520
Kluay,

218
00:17:50,360 --> 00:17:51,440
I'm sorry.

219
00:17:52,840 --> 00:17:55,040
From now on, no matter what happens,

220
00:17:56,480 --> 00:17:58,360
I'll never let go of your hand again.

221
00:18:04,440 --> 00:18:07,520
Think about what I said.

222
00:18:07,600 --> 00:18:09,320
Think about it.

223
00:18:22,560 --> 00:18:25,400
Yes. That's good.

224
00:18:27,920 --> 00:18:31,200
Alright, then please hurry back.

225
00:18:31,280 --> 00:18:34,000
Ms. Kluay is safe now.
She's not hurt at all.

226
00:18:34,080 --> 00:18:35,320
- He found her?
- Yeah.

227
00:18:35,400 --> 00:18:36,600
- She's safe, right?
- Yes.

228
00:18:36,680 --> 00:18:38,560
Thank you, Arnon. Thank you so much.

229
00:18:38,640 --> 00:18:41,320
- Hm.
- Thank you, Mr. Supol and everyone.

230
00:18:41,400 --> 00:18:43,400
Don't worry. How is Mrs. Wanee?

231
00:18:43,480 --> 00:18:45,320
You're hugging?

232
00:18:45,400 --> 00:18:46,840
Alright.

233
00:18:46,920 --> 00:18:48,920
The doctor just called.

234
00:18:49,000 --> 00:18:52,200
She's out of danger now,
but she needs to rest.

235
00:18:52,280 --> 00:18:53,640
No visitors allowed.

236
00:18:53,720 --> 00:18:55,120
But she's safe, right?

237
00:18:55,200 --> 00:18:56,600
With the utmost respect,

238
00:18:56,680 --> 00:18:59,120
the doctor said she's safe.
Nothing to worry about.

239
00:19:02,480 --> 00:19:03,720
You can keep hugging.

240
00:19:14,280 --> 00:19:19,120
That lawyer said Warat
is transferring his shares. Did you hear?

241
00:19:19,200 --> 00:19:21,000
<i>Yeah, he called me too.</i>

242
00:19:23,080 --> 00:19:25,480
Why is he backing down like this?
Why is he transferring the shares?

243
00:19:26,760 --> 00:19:29,680
<i>Or did he find out</i>
<i>we were planning to take him down?</i>

244
00:19:31,520 --> 00:19:33,800
Then who is he transferring them to?

245
00:19:33,880 --> 00:19:35,480
<i>Waree Vanich.</i>

246
00:19:37,360 --> 00:19:40,680
Don't tell me he already knows
that Kluay is Waree.

247
00:19:40,760 --> 00:19:43,360
<i>If that's true,</i>
<i>then it works in our favor.</i>

248
00:19:43,440 --> 00:19:46,480
I… I didn't do it.

249
00:19:46,560 --> 00:19:48,760
<i>Oh, why not, Mr. Sin?</i>

250
00:19:50,320 --> 00:19:52,280
I find her disgusting.

251
00:19:52,360 --> 00:19:55,960
<i>Come on, you could have just</i>
<i>closed your eyes and done it.</i>

252
00:19:56,040 --> 00:19:59,960
<i>Did Warat transfer all his shares to you?</i>

253
00:20:12,640 --> 00:20:17,360
The house is neat and well-kept.

254
00:20:17,440 --> 00:20:20,200
You've done a great job, Anong.
You take good care of the house.

255
00:20:21,440 --> 00:20:24,880
- Yes, Mr. Rut. It's my duty.
- Mm.

256
00:20:26,400 --> 00:20:27,520
Well, Anong.

257
00:20:28,200 --> 00:20:31,520
I want to apologize

258
00:20:34,080 --> 00:20:37,160
for how I treated you before.

259
00:20:37,240 --> 00:20:39,160
I doubted you.

260
00:20:40,440 --> 00:20:43,840
Now I understand everything.

261
00:20:43,920 --> 00:20:46,160
Everything you did

262
00:20:46,240 --> 00:20:49,880
was for our family.

263
00:20:52,120 --> 00:20:52,960
Yes.

264
00:20:53,840 --> 00:20:58,600
I did it all for our family.

265
00:21:00,080 --> 00:21:03,880
Once we sort out Warat's assets,

266
00:21:04,760 --> 00:21:07,360
we should move to a new house.

267
00:21:07,440 --> 00:21:10,000
Somewhere bigger and nicer.

268
00:21:10,640 --> 00:21:11,760
What do you think?

269
00:21:12,920 --> 00:21:14,320
What kind of house do you like?

270
00:21:15,440 --> 00:21:18,080
Or we can move to another city.

271
00:21:18,160 --> 00:21:21,200
Maybe Chiang Mai or Phuket.

272
00:21:21,280 --> 00:21:24,040
The mountains or the sea.

273
00:21:24,120 --> 00:21:26,680
Whatever you like. You can tell me.

274
00:21:27,560 --> 00:21:28,400
Is that good?

275
00:21:29,160 --> 00:21:30,520
Right now,

276
00:21:31,280 --> 00:21:33,720
Warat is transferring all his shares

277
00:21:34,320 --> 00:21:36,720
- to someone else.
- Hey?

278
00:21:49,160 --> 00:21:50,720
Right?

279
00:21:51,800 --> 00:21:54,000
How could that happen?

280
00:21:54,960 --> 00:21:56,840
If that's true,

281
00:21:56,920 --> 00:21:59,520
then Sin will get nothing.

282
00:21:59,600 --> 00:22:03,120
The only way for Sin
to get everything back

283
00:22:04,360 --> 00:22:06,280
is for you and Warat

284
00:22:07,080 --> 00:22:08,720
to die.

285
00:22:13,720 --> 00:22:17,240
Then Vanich Mall will belong to me alone.

286
00:22:40,720 --> 00:22:42,760
I'm sorry.

287
00:22:45,160 --> 00:22:46,520
What?

288
00:22:51,200 --> 00:22:54,320
You can drop me off here.

289
00:22:59,440 --> 00:23:01,280
What are you saying, Kluay?

290
00:23:03,440 --> 00:23:05,000
I…

291
00:23:06,040 --> 00:23:07,280
I think…

292
00:23:21,840 --> 00:23:24,320
You want to get off here?

293
00:23:27,120 --> 00:23:28,600
Did he hurt you?

294
00:23:30,400 --> 00:23:32,400
No, I'm not hurt.

295
00:23:34,400 --> 00:23:35,640
Then what's bothering you?

296
00:23:35,720 --> 00:23:40,480
I don't know what happened last night

297
00:23:40,560 --> 00:23:42,360
when I was asleep.

298
00:23:45,320 --> 00:23:48,760
Nothing happened. Don't overthink it.

299
00:23:49,640 --> 00:23:52,160
But… what if…

300
00:23:52,240 --> 00:23:53,760
We slept together last night.

301
00:23:55,200 --> 00:23:58,960
I've lost my dignity.
I'm no longer worthy of you.

302
00:24:01,960 --> 00:24:03,480
What is dignity?

303
00:24:04,640 --> 00:24:07,160
And what does it mean to lose it?

304
00:24:09,600 --> 00:24:11,920
Listen to me. It doesn't matter.

305
00:24:14,200 --> 00:24:16,160
I love you for who you are.

306
00:24:17,200 --> 00:24:21,600
I love your heart.
What era do you think this is?

307
00:24:25,440 --> 00:24:27,720
I don't care what you've been through.

308
00:24:30,960 --> 00:24:33,240
What matters
is that you're here with me now

309
00:24:34,480 --> 00:24:35,440
and I love you.

310
00:24:36,840 --> 00:24:39,120
What about your grandmother?

311
00:24:41,360 --> 00:24:43,160
Don't worry about anyone else.

312
00:24:44,760 --> 00:24:47,120
We have each other.
We take care of each other.

313
00:24:48,120 --> 00:24:49,720
We stay together forever.

314
00:24:50,480 --> 00:24:54,560
That's what matters most to me.

315
00:24:57,640 --> 00:24:58,560
Okay?

316
00:25:00,680 --> 00:25:01,760
Thank you.

317
00:25:05,000 --> 00:25:06,680
- But Sin…
- Kluay,

318
00:25:06,760 --> 00:25:09,280
stop saying that bastard's name.

319
00:25:09,360 --> 00:25:10,800
It makes me sick.

320
00:25:13,520 --> 00:25:15,560
He called me Waree.

321
00:25:50,000 --> 00:25:51,000
What are you doing, Aunt Nong?

322
00:25:52,320 --> 00:25:54,280
I spilled some water, Sin.

323
00:25:54,360 --> 00:25:56,480
- Then I'll help.
- Oh, no need.

324
00:25:58,800 --> 00:26:02,360
Go sit down.
I have something to talk to you about.

325
00:26:03,200 --> 00:26:04,040
Okay.

326
00:26:17,160 --> 00:26:18,000
Oh.

327
00:26:18,080 --> 00:26:20,800
With the utmost respect, miss,
are you hurt anywhere?

328
00:26:22,680 --> 00:26:25,480
- Mr. Supol, what's wrong?
- Well.

329
00:26:25,560 --> 00:26:27,400
Why are you acting so strange with me?

330
00:26:29,320 --> 00:26:31,280
- Kluay.
- Hm?

331
00:26:33,640 --> 00:26:35,120
Listen to us carefully.

332
00:26:35,760 --> 00:26:38,160
What's wrong with everyone?

333
00:26:39,240 --> 00:26:41,040
I don't know if you'll believe me.

334
00:26:42,000 --> 00:26:45,440
But I, and everyone here,

335
00:26:46,600 --> 00:26:49,600
have looked into everything, documents,

336
00:26:50,200 --> 00:26:51,720
police records,

337
00:26:53,080 --> 00:26:55,880
the unidentified bodies foundation.

338
00:26:57,760 --> 00:26:59,360
Every piece of information

339
00:27:00,200 --> 00:27:01,920
that we found…

340
00:27:02,560 --> 00:27:03,400
Yes?

341
00:27:04,120 --> 00:27:05,720
…says you are not Boonsita.

342
00:27:08,600 --> 00:27:10,280
I'm not…

343
00:27:11,520 --> 00:27:12,360
Kluay.

344
00:27:14,480 --> 00:27:16,440
How is that possible?

345
00:27:16,520 --> 00:27:18,800
How can I not be Boonsita?

346
00:27:20,600 --> 00:27:22,520
You are Waree Vanich,

347
00:27:22,600 --> 00:27:24,800
the only heir of the Vanich family.

348
00:27:26,920 --> 00:27:30,280
The only daughter
of Mr. Wichan and Ms. Ampha.

349
00:27:32,280 --> 00:27:33,680
Which means…

350
00:27:36,120 --> 00:27:38,280
you are Grandma's real granddaughter.

351
00:27:40,200 --> 00:27:41,200
Uh…

352
00:27:46,600 --> 00:27:49,080
What kind of game is everyone playing?

353
00:27:49,760 --> 00:27:51,840
This isn't funny.

354
00:27:55,040 --> 00:27:57,480
With the utmost respect, miss,

355
00:27:57,560 --> 00:28:01,000
everything Mr. Warat said is true.

356
00:28:09,760 --> 00:28:11,000
Mr. Arnon,

357
00:28:11,720 --> 00:28:15,720
are all of you ganging up to prank me?

358
00:28:18,160 --> 00:28:20,200
It's true, Ms. Kluay.

359
00:28:23,640 --> 00:28:27,600
Som, this isn't true, right?

360
00:28:29,600 --> 00:28:30,760
It's true.

361
00:28:54,640 --> 00:28:55,600
What is going on?

362
00:28:59,120 --> 00:29:00,120
Calm down, Kluay.

363
00:29:00,200 --> 00:29:01,880
I am calm.

364
00:29:03,720 --> 00:29:08,160
Why? Why is everyone treating me
like this? I'm still the same Kluay.

365
00:29:09,040 --> 00:29:12,640
They're probably just happy
that you're Waree.

366
00:29:13,400 --> 00:29:16,520
They probably never thought
they'd ever find Waree again.

367
00:29:16,600 --> 00:29:17,880
And in the end,

368
00:29:19,000 --> 00:29:20,640
they found you, found Waree.

369
00:29:21,680 --> 00:29:23,440
Of course they're happy.

370
00:29:24,840 --> 00:29:29,040
But why does everyone
have to act like that?

371
00:29:30,240 --> 00:29:32,560
Why judge someone

372
00:29:32,640 --> 00:29:35,680
by their surname, their name,
or whose child or grandchild they are?

373
00:29:35,760 --> 00:29:37,480
Why not judge them by their actions?

374
00:29:38,840 --> 00:29:41,120
They are judging by the truth.

375
00:29:43,400 --> 00:29:44,880
You are Kluay.

376
00:29:45,480 --> 00:29:47,120
Think about it.

377
00:29:48,120 --> 00:29:50,720
If you came in as a bad person,

378
00:29:51,600 --> 00:29:52,840
selfish

379
00:29:53,520 --> 00:29:57,080
and cruel,

380
00:29:58,000 --> 00:30:02,320
do you think people would be happy
to find Waree?

381
00:30:03,840 --> 00:30:04,720
Right?

382
00:30:08,880 --> 00:30:12,840
What if the truth is I'm not Waree?

383
00:30:16,240 --> 00:30:19,680
Actually, it doesn't matter

384
00:30:20,280 --> 00:30:21,640
whether you are

385
00:30:22,800 --> 00:30:24,400
Waree or not.

386
00:30:25,160 --> 00:30:26,920
Everyone who loves you

387
00:30:28,040 --> 00:30:29,520
loves you because you're Kluay.

388
00:30:31,400 --> 00:30:33,160
But from the evidence we have now,

389
00:30:33,240 --> 00:30:35,440
it can't be anything else.

390
00:30:36,960 --> 00:30:39,760
You just have to accept and understand it.

391
00:30:40,680 --> 00:30:42,800
And if that really is the truth…

392
00:30:43,760 --> 00:30:46,120
Then you're Waree Vanich.

393
00:30:53,240 --> 00:30:55,040
And I'm just an ordinary man.

394
00:31:10,960 --> 00:31:12,800
Please take care of Grandma for me.

395
00:31:15,360 --> 00:31:17,200
What do you mean?

396
00:31:21,720 --> 00:31:23,000
I've done everything

397
00:31:23,960 --> 00:31:25,280
that I should do.

398
00:31:30,360 --> 00:31:31,560
I…

399
00:31:33,600 --> 00:31:37,320
should go back to where I belong.

400
00:31:38,120 --> 00:31:41,080
I'm just Mr. Sarut's son.
Just an ordinary man.

401
00:31:47,960 --> 00:31:49,760
Didn't you tell me

402
00:31:51,800 --> 00:31:54,040
that no matter
whose child we were born as,

403
00:31:55,160 --> 00:31:57,840
the best thing is that
we have each other right now?

404
00:32:01,800 --> 00:32:04,120
I'm still the same Kluay.

405
00:32:08,840 --> 00:32:11,280
And you're still my Warat.

406
00:32:13,160 --> 00:32:16,320
Nothing can change that truth.

407
00:32:25,160 --> 00:32:26,880
Do you love me?

408
00:32:29,840 --> 00:32:30,680
Mm.

409
00:32:32,840 --> 00:32:34,480
You changed the mood so fast.

410
00:32:36,040 --> 00:32:38,440
I asked if you love me.

411
00:32:39,040 --> 00:32:39,960
I do.

412
00:32:41,080 --> 00:32:45,240
Do you love me because I'm Kluay,
or because I'm Waree?

413
00:32:48,920 --> 00:32:50,160
Because you're Waree.

414
00:32:50,240 --> 00:32:51,280
Hey!

415
00:32:51,360 --> 00:32:52,800
How could you?

416
00:32:53,440 --> 00:32:56,320
I'm joking.
I love you because you're Kluay.

417
00:32:56,400 --> 00:32:57,840
See?

418
00:32:58,600 --> 00:33:01,200
I love you because you're Mr. Warat too.

419
00:33:03,560 --> 00:33:06,480
Not because you have any wealth.

420
00:33:15,000 --> 00:33:16,440
Aw.

421
00:33:16,520 --> 00:33:17,520
Crazy.

422
00:33:19,080 --> 00:33:21,720
- I'm blushing.
- Blushing?

423
00:33:22,720 --> 00:33:24,160
Don't cry anymore.

424
00:33:24,800 --> 00:33:26,640
- I'm not crying.
- Alright, you're not.

425
00:33:32,760 --> 00:33:35,000
I'll believe everything you say

426
00:33:35,760 --> 00:33:37,760
because I trust you.

427
00:33:42,560 --> 00:33:43,640
So…

428
00:33:45,160 --> 00:33:47,040
stay with me for a long, long time.

429
00:33:48,760 --> 00:33:50,480
- Okay.
- Okay now?

430
00:33:51,880 --> 00:33:52,800
Okay.

431
00:33:55,560 --> 00:33:57,160
- Let's go.
- Where?

432
00:33:57,240 --> 00:33:59,360
Let's go find something to eat.
I'm hungry.

433
00:34:03,520 --> 00:34:05,640
- What do you want to eat?
- Not telling.

434
00:34:05,720 --> 00:34:09,360
How will I know where to take you
if you don't tell me?

435
00:34:09,440 --> 00:34:10,480
I'm not going.

436
00:34:10,560 --> 00:34:13,120
But you said you were hungry.

437
00:34:18,400 --> 00:34:21,840
How do you think
Mr. Warat and Kluay are doing?

438
00:34:22,840 --> 00:34:26,080
I think they must be very shocked
that something like this happening

439
00:34:26,800 --> 00:34:30,920
Of course she'll be shocked.
It comes with responsibility too.

440
00:34:32,600 --> 00:34:33,440
Right.

441
00:34:35,400 --> 00:34:38,440
A responsibility
that carries so much weight.

442
00:34:38,520 --> 00:34:40,199
Suddenly she's becoming

443
00:34:40,280 --> 00:34:43,560
the heir of a billionaire family
with a huge inheritance.

444
00:34:43,639 --> 00:34:45,400
She really has to give up a lot for that.

445
00:34:45,920 --> 00:34:49,360
Give up what? I'd give it up.
Is there anything for me to give up?

446
00:34:50,520 --> 00:34:51,880
Hey.

447
00:34:54,000 --> 00:34:56,280
Oh, Mr. Warat

448
00:34:56,360 --> 00:34:58,560
and Mrs. Wanee are lucky

449
00:34:58,640 --> 00:35:01,160
that it's Kluay.

450
00:35:01,240 --> 00:35:03,560
If it had been just anyone,

451
00:35:03,640 --> 00:35:05,360
it would've been a lot harder.

452
00:35:06,360 --> 00:35:09,760
True. If it were Ameena…

453
00:35:09,840 --> 00:35:10,800
Ouch.

454
00:35:12,400 --> 00:35:15,720
I mean Ms. Kluay and Mr. Warat

455
00:35:16,480 --> 00:35:18,280
are very well matched.

456
00:35:18,360 --> 00:35:21,080
They met each other

457
00:35:22,680 --> 00:35:26,440
without knowing who they really were,
without knowing each other's surnames,

458
00:35:27,280 --> 00:35:29,720
backgrounds, or where they came from.

459
00:35:29,800 --> 00:35:31,640
I think no matter what,
those two would still love each other.

460
00:35:33,720 --> 00:35:35,440
That's true.

461
00:35:36,040 --> 00:35:38,440
Everything will be

462
00:35:39,720 --> 00:35:41,320
the way it's supposed to be.

463
00:35:42,440 --> 00:35:44,840
Everything will fall into place.

464
00:35:45,840 --> 00:35:47,400
- Exactly.
- Mm.

465
00:36:01,480 --> 00:36:03,360
Aunt Nong, is there something
you want to talk to me about?

466
00:36:04,800 --> 00:36:06,000
Sin.

467
00:36:06,960 --> 00:36:10,040
Right now is the time
we have to make a decision quickly.

468
00:36:11,040 --> 00:36:13,120
You know everything already?

469
00:36:14,720 --> 00:36:16,440
Chatchai told me everything.

470
00:36:19,280 --> 00:36:21,000
Warat is about
to transfer the shares to Kluay.

471
00:36:21,720 --> 00:36:23,120
If that happens,

472
00:36:23,200 --> 00:36:25,840
everything we built will be gone.

473
00:36:26,720 --> 00:36:30,760
That's why I wanted to talk to you.

474
00:36:31,360 --> 00:36:34,560
If Wanee wakes up and signs,
all the assets will belong to Kluay.

475
00:36:35,560 --> 00:36:38,920
So we have to settle everything

476
00:36:39,000 --> 00:36:41,360
before Wanee wakes up.

477
00:36:42,880 --> 00:36:45,120
Auntie, what are you going to do?

478
00:37:14,000 --> 00:37:15,880
Hey! Hey?

479
00:37:36,320 --> 00:37:37,600
Hey!

480
00:37:37,680 --> 00:37:39,960
Anong! Anong!

481
00:37:40,040 --> 00:37:42,800
Anong, what the hell are you doing?!

482
00:37:43,800 --> 00:37:44,760
Anong!

483
00:37:47,320 --> 00:37:51,000
If Warat dies,
all the shares will go to Uncle Rut.

484
00:37:51,880 --> 00:37:53,040
And what if Uncle Rut dies?

485
00:37:54,280 --> 00:37:56,680
Then all the shares will go to us.

486
00:37:56,760 --> 00:37:58,320
NEXT EPISODE

487
00:37:58,400 --> 00:37:59,600
Bow to me.

488
00:38:01,160 --> 00:38:02,480
Bow!

489
00:38:10,680 --> 00:38:12,840
Mr. Arnon, let's go to Mr. Sarut's house.

490
00:38:12,920 --> 00:38:14,520
Mr. Warat is at Mr. Sarut's house?

491
00:38:14,600 --> 00:38:16,200
Why Sarut's house?

492
00:38:18,200 --> 00:38:19,480
Warat, watch out!

493
00:38:20,240 --> 00:38:21,320
- Ugh!
- Warat!

494
00:38:21,400 --> 00:38:23,960
Help! Warat!

495
00:40:49,800 --> 00:40:51,560
Subtitle translation by: Panuwat Baikeawon
